      • fireTreeNodesChanged

        protected void fireTreeNodesChanged(SortedTreeModel.TNode parent,
                                    SortedTreeModel.TNode[] children)
        Fires a TreeModelEvent for "nodes-changed". This should take place when user objects under the given nodes have changed (display related) content.

        parent == null indicates the root node changed; in this case children is irrelevant.

        Parameters:
        parent - TNode parent of modified nodes
        children - TNode[] child objects modified
